item.description:
Constructions # ~ㄹ/을 수 있/없다 is used to create the meaning of &ldquo;one can&hellip;&rdquo; or &ldquo;one cannot&hellip;&rdquo;
~고 있다 is attached to verbs to give it a meaning of &ldquo;I am ___ing.&rdquo;
~(으)면 is used to create the meaning of &ldquo;when&rdquo; or &ldquo;if.
~ㄹ/을수록 is attached to verbs, adjectives and 이다 to indicate that, as one situation changes to some degree, another situation is affected and also changes to that degree.
